      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Fair enough, I guess we need to roll back to 0.63 until it is fixed, and work out how to report the issue.\n\nIn config.yaml if I set the DESIGN_NAME to `uart_tx` and remove chip_top and chip_core I still get the issue, so that is getting towards a small repro.  But I'm not quite sure how to then wrap that up into something I can report to yosys",
      "author": {
        "id": "691780627338625077",
        "name": "rebelmike",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "RebelMike",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [],
